---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Privacy';
const description = 'How BeyondBorderGroup handles the information you share with us.';
---

<Layout locale={locale} route="privacy" title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="legal-hero__title balance">Privacy</h1>
      <p class="lead">How BeyondBorderGroup handles the information you share with us.</p>
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated 10 May 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow legal-prose">
      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        BeyondBorderGroup Ltd is a company registered in Hong Kong. We are the holding entity for a group
        of cross-border agencies, including BeyondBorderGroup, BeyondBridge, TheRedScroll, ChinaWebFoundry,
        BeyondCompass, HubStudio, and Nuvora Studio. This policy covers beyondbordergroup.com and the data
        we collect through it. Each agency may publish its own policy on its own site.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        Two kinds of data. The first is information you give us directly. When you fill in the contact
        form, ask for a proposal, or work with us on a project, we keep what you share: name, email, phone,
        company, the brief you describe, and anything you choose to add.
      </p>
      <p>
        The second is information your browser leaves behind during a visit. Standard server logs (IP
        address, user agent, time of visit, pages viewed), and a small set of cookies described in our
        Cookie Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <p>We use what you give us to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>answer your inquiry and follow up on it,</li>
        <li>deliver the work you have hired us for,</li>
        <li>operate and improve the site,</li>
        <li>send marketing only when you have asked for it, and stop when you ask us to stop,</li>
        <li>handle invoicing and contracts,</li>
        <li>meet our legal and tax obligations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Server logs and cookies are aggregated for performance and traffic patterns. They are not tied
        to individual visitors and we do not try to combine them with the personal data above.
      </p>

      <h2>Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal data. We do not rent it. The people who see it are the BBG team, the
        relevant agency team inside the group, and the small number of vendors we use to run the business
        (email, hosting, accounting, payments, video calls). Those vendors are bound by confidentiality
        agreements and by their own privacy terms. We will hand over data when a court or regulator with
        proper jurisdiction asks us to, and not otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        We run reasonable technical and organizational measures: encrypted transit, access controls,
        vendors with comparable standards. No system on the open internet is perfectly safe, and we will
        not pretend ours is. If we suffer a breach that affects your data, we will notify you and the
        regulator as required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>You can ask us to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>show you what we hold on you,</li>
        <li>correct it if it is wrong,</li>
        <li>delete it, when no contract or law requires us to keep it,</li>
        <li>stop using it for marketing,</li>
        <li>withdraw a consent you previously gave.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hello@beyondbordergroup.com">hello@beyondbordergroup.com</a>. We aim to
        reply within 30 days. If you are unhappy with our reply, the Hong Kong Privacy Commissioner is
        the regulator who oversees us under the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        This site is built for businesses. We do not knowingly collect personal data from anyone under
        16. If you believe a child has sent us data, write to us and we will delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party sites</h2>
      <p>
        We link to other sites: agency sites in our group, partner pages, social platforms. Once you
        click out, the rules of those sites apply, not ours.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise this policy. The date at the top tells you when. Material changes will be flagged
        on the site so you can read them before you decide what to do.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        BeyondBorderGroup Ltd<br />
        Hong Kong SAR<br />
        <a href="mailto:hello@beyondbordergroup.com">hello@beyondbordergroup.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-hero {
    padding: clamp(5rem, 12vh, 8rem) 0 clamp(2rem, 5vh, 3.5rem);
    background: var(--bbg-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bbg-border);
  }
  .legal-hero__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 0.5rem, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-4);
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal-meta {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--bbg-text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-3);
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
  }
  .legal-prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .legal-prose p,
  .legal-prose ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--bbg-text);
  }
  .legal-prose ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .legal-prose li { margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }
  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--bbg-blue);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal-prose a:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
</style>
